itemDescription: Welsh rugby union and rugby league footballer

wikipedia_page.main: Thomas Emlyn Gwynne (fourth ¼ 1898 – fourth ¼ 1962) was a Welsh rugby union and professional rugby league footballer who played in the 1920s and 1930s. He played club level rugby union (RU) for Mountain Ash RFC and Swansea RFC, and representative level rugby league (RL) for both Great Britain, Wales and Glamorgan, and at club level for Hull F.C. (Heritage No.), as a wing, i.e. number 2 or 5.
